# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: HassarPath | Scene: JaeidPath6
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Sarah had finished the last of her tasks around the house and was preparing to make dinner."
    new "Sarah had finished the last of her tasks around the house and was preparing to make dinner."

    old "She still hadn't much practice, and she doubted her hosts were being entirely truthful in liking it, but she still kept at it."
    new "She still hadn't much practice, and she doubted her hosts were being entirely truthful in liking it, but she still kept at it."

    old "Only, just before she could begin, Jaeid arrived home."
    new "Only, just before she could begin, Jaeid arrived home."

    old "Aah, Sarah, there you are."
    new "Aah, Sarah, there you are."

    old "Yes, I didn't have any other appointments today."
    new "Yes, I didn't have any other appointments today."

    old "Jaeid awkwardly smiled at her joke."
    new "Jaeid awkwardly smiled at her joke."

    old "How has your day been? I haven't seen much of you today. I was hoping we could have dinner together again."
    new "How has your day been? I haven't seen much of you today. I was hoping we could have dinner together again."

    old "That is actually why I came to see you."
    new "That is actually why I came to see you."

    old "He paused for a moment, as if to consider his words."
    new "He paused for a moment, as if to consider his words."

    old "The Khan has extended an invitation tonight."
    new "The Khan has extended an invitation tonight."

    old "An invitation?"
    new "An invitation?"

    old "To myself...and you as well."
    new "To myself...and you as well."

    old "Sarah tried to make sense of what Jaeid was saying."
    new "Sarah tried to make sense of what Jaeid was saying."

    old "I...the Khan? Why does he want to see me?"
    new "I...the Khan? Why does he want to see me?"

    old "Sarah stepped closer to Jaeid."
    new "Sarah stepped closer to Jaeid."

    old "Am I in danger?"
    new "Am I in danger?"

    old "She had managed to avoid the Khan's grasp only days earlier...was it all for nothing?"
    new "She had managed to avoid the Khan's grasp only days earlier...was it all for nothing?"

    old "No, Sarah. I promise you, no harm will come to you."
    new "No, Sarah. I promise you, no harm will come to you."

    old "Then why? If I am but a slave, what purpose does he have for me?"
    new "Then why? If I am but a slave, what purpose does he have for me?"

    old "Jaeid looked away, seemingly ashamed."
    new "Jaeid looked away, seemingly ashamed."

    old "The Khan...he is hosting a feast to celebrate our victory."
    new "The Khan...he is hosting a feast to celebrate our victory."

    old "Sarah looked Jaeid until he met her eyes."
    new "Sarah looked Jaeid until he met her eyes."

    old "Your victory...over Rosanna."
    new "Your victory...over Rosanna."

    old "Yes, Sarah. He wishes to celebrate the victory of the Tribes."
    new "Yes, Sarah. He wishes to celebrate the victory of the Tribes."

    old "What does that mean, exactly?"
    new "What does that mean, exactly?"

    old "It means a feast for everyone of import that took part in the campaign."
    new "It means a feast for everyone of import that took part in the campaign."

    old "It means distributing loot."
    new "It means distributing loot."

    old "Loot."
    new "Loot."

    old "Sarah repeated the word. It meant more than what it might mean to someone from Rosanna."
    new "Sarah repeated the word. It meant more than what it might mean to someone from Rosanna."

    old "It meant wealth and land, sure. But Sarah also knew the customs of the Tribes well by now."
    new "It meant wealth and land, sure. But Sarah also knew the customs of the Tribes well by now."

    old "It also meant women."
    new "It also meant women."

    old "They will distribute what has been conquered among those according to their rank."
    new "They will distribute what has been conquered among those according to their rank."

    old "Sarah nodded. Whatever disgust she might feel was meaningless. She could do nothing to stop it."
    new "Sarah nodded. Whatever disgust she might feel was meaningless. She could do nothing to stop it."

    old "Is that it?"
    new "Is that it?"

    old "Lastly, they will also crown a new governor."
    new "Lastly, they will also crown a new governor."

    old "A governor?"
    new "A governor?"

    old "For the new province."
    new "For the new province."

    old "It took Sarah a moment to understand."
    new "It took Sarah a moment to understand."

    old "Rosanna will be..."
    new "Rosanna will be..."

    old "Her nation, had not just been broken and defeated. It would soon cease to exist at all."
    new "Her nation, had not just been broken and defeated. It would soon cease to exist at all."

    old "Rosanna, the nation of herself, her father, and a family line that chained back centuries."
    new "Rosanna, the nation of herself, her father, and a family line that chained back centuries."

    old "Now, to be made a province to one man's mad empire of conquest."
    new "Now, to be made a province to one man's mad empire of conquest."

    old "I...who will it be?"
    new "I...who will it be?"

    old "I do not know those details yet, only that the Khan has invited me to attend and wished for you to come as well."
    new "I do not know those details yet, only that the Khan has invited me to attend and wished for you to come as well."

    old "He asked for me explicitly?"
    new "He asked for me explicitly?"

    old "I would not expose you to this if I had a choice...but my Khan commands."
    new "I would not expose you to this if I had a choice...but my Khan commands."

    old "Sarah looked about the room as she considered."
    new "Sarah looked about the room as she considered."

    old "Refusing the Khan's request was no option, not even for someone as Jaeid, let alone for a slave like her."
    new "Refusing the Khan's request was no option, not even for someone as Jaeid, let alone for a slave like her."

    old "But you're worried."
    new "But you're worried."

    old "She could see it in his face."
    new "She could see it in his face."

    old "Because the Tribes...we are a people of conquest. Forged in the fires of war."
    new "Because the Tribes...we are a people of conquest. Forged in the fires of war."

    old "The Tribesmen enjoy conquering their enemies, but they also enjoy breaking them. Humiliating them."
    new "The Tribesmen enjoy conquering their enemies, but they also enjoy breaking them. Humiliating them."

    old "Humiliating?"
    new "Humiliating?"

    old "Yes. They believe it is required for an effective conquest."
    new "Yes. They believe it is required for an effective conquest."

    old "You must not only defeat your enemies physically, but also spiritually."
    new "You must not only defeat your enemies physically, but also spiritually."

    old "So they play their games."
    new "So they play their games."

    old "Jaeid gestured at Sarah's slave clothes."
    new "Jaeid gestured at Sarah's slave clothes."

    old "Even your clothes...these are not designed by accident. They are made to degrade you."
    new "Even your clothes...these are not designed by accident. They are made to degrade you."

    old "So that you might degrade yourself in your own mind. Break your own spirit and become the slave within as you are without."
    new "So that you might degrade yourself in your own mind. Break your own spirit and become the slave within as you are without."

    old "So you are afraid that they will hurt me?"
    new "So you are afraid that they will hurt me?"

    old "No...they cannot harm you directly."
    new "No...they cannot harm you directly."

    old "Because on the one hand, you are mine and to do so would be an insult to me. They won't wish to do so."
    new "Because on the one hand, you are mine and to do so would be an insult to me. They won't wish to do so."

    old "Also, to hurt you directly would imply that you are of any value, and they will not wish to suggest that either."
    new "Also, to hurt you directly would imply that you are of any value, and they will not wish to suggest that either."

    old "They will humiliate you. Rosanna. Your people."
    new "They will humiliate you. Rosanna. Your people."

    old "I think they might hope that you will break under the insults. That you will lash out in a moment of emotion."
    new "I think they might hope that you will break under the insults. That you will lash out in a moment of emotion."

    old "And then they will have their excuse."
    new "And then they will have their excuse."

    old "If you insult them, by words or by actions, they will have the excuse they need."
    new "If you insult them, by words or by actions, they will have the excuse they need."

    old "The excuse...to hurt me?"
    new "The excuse...to hurt me?"

    old "As I said before, if I could avoid it, I would not have put you in this position."
    new "As I said before, if I could avoid it, I would not have put you in this position."

    old "I understand. Thank you for warning me."
    new "I understand. Thank you for warning me."

    old "But Sarah, you must understand...you cannot give them a reason. None at all or they will punish you for it."
    new "But Sarah, you must understand...you cannot give them a reason. None at all or they will punish you for it."

    old "Sarah showed a pained smile."
    new "Sarah showed a pained smile."

    old "Don't worry, Jaeid. Smiling and pretending like everything is fine is what I was taught to do from birth."
    new "Don't worry, Jaeid. Smiling and pretending like everything is fine is what I was taught to do from birth."

    old "When they arrived later that night at the hall of feasts, Sarah struggled to make sense of the sight."
    new "When they arrived later that night at the hall of feasts, Sarah struggled to make sense of the sight."

    old "She had never seen a room this vast in all of her life."
    new "She had never seen a room this vast in all of her life."

    old "And swarming everywhere, more people than she had ever seen gathered under one roof."
    new "And swarming everywhere, more people than she had ever seen gathered under one roof."

    old "When Jaeid had told her, only the most important people would attend, Sarah had never dared to imagine this many people."
    new "When Jaeid had told her, only the most important people would attend, Sarah had never dared to imagine this many people."

    old "Seeing the Horde in all its strength, Sarah saw that it was foolishness that they might ever defeat warriors like these."
    new "Seeing the Horde in all its strength, Sarah saw that it was foolishness that they might ever defeat warriors like these."

    old "The Khan has invited us to sit upon the dais."
    new "The Khan has invited us to sit upon the dais."

    old "Jaied gestured towards the far end of the room where the Khan sat, along with his family and closest advisors."
    new "Jaied gestured towards the far end of the room where the Khan sat, along with his family and closest advisors."

    old "Tell Jaeid about what happened at the market"
    new "Tell Jaeid about what happened at the market"

    old "The events earlier that day, the Tribesman at the market..."
    new "The events earlier that day, the Tribesman at the market..."

    old "They had weighed on Sarah's mind all day."
    new "They had weighed on Sarah's mind all day."

    old "Jaeid..."
    new "Jaeid..."

    old "Sarah felt her mouth go dry."
    new "Sarah felt her mouth go dry."

    old "She did her best to gather her courage."
    new "She did her best to gather her courage."

    old "Something happened today..."
    new "Something happened today..."

    old "Jaeid looked at her and frowned."
    new "Jaeid looked at her and frowned."

    old "What do you speak of?"
    new "What do you speak of?"

    old "Would he be angry with her? Would he hit her. Please Gods, thought Sarah, let him forgive me."
    new "Would he be angry with her? Would he hit her. Please Gods, thought Sarah, let him forgive me."

    old "At the market..."
    new "At the market..."

    old "Sarah told Jaeid everything that had happened."
    new "Sarah told Jaeid everything that had happened."

    old "When she finished her story, she looked him in the eyes."
    new "When she finished her story, she looked him in the eyes."

    old "Jaeid only smiled, and his kind eyes never wavered."
    new "Jaeid only smiled, and his kind eyes never wavered."

    old "Sarah, it was not your fault, but you were right to speak to me about it."
    new "Sarah, it was not your fault, but you were right to speak to me about it."

    old "You...forgive me?"
    new "You...forgive me?"

    old "There is nothing for you to be forgiven for."
    new "There is nothing for you to be forgiven for."

    old "I will make things right."
    new "I will make things right."

    old "He placed one hand on her shoulder."
    new "He placed one hand on her shoulder."

    old "For tonight, set it out of your mind and focus on what is important. Your safety."
    new "For tonight, set it out of your mind and focus on what is important. Your safety."

    old "She saw him smile again, the way he only ever seemed to do with her."
    new "She saw him smile again, the way he only ever seemed to do with her."

    old "Forget it, thought Sarah."
    new "Forget it, thought Sarah."

    old "Better not to make more of it than it was."
    new "Better not to make more of it than it was."

    old "Jaeid held her hand as they walked down the aisle towards the dais."
    new "Jaeid held her hand as they walked down the aisle towards the dais."

    old "As they walked, Sarah looked from side to side."
    new "As they walked, Sarah looked from side to side."

    old "Everywhere that she looked, she saw that the feast was well under way."
    new "Everywhere that she looked, she saw that the feast was well under way."

    old "Soldiers sat around their tables, loudly celebrating."
    new "Soldiers sat around their tables, loudly celebrating."

    old "Cups of wine poured down their throat, and not a moment after they drained them, they were refilled."
    new "Cups of wine poured down their throat, and not a moment after they drained them, they were refilled."

    old "Refilled by slaves."
    new "Refilled by slaves."

    old "Sarah could see the room filled with them, wearing the same slave clothes as herself."
    new "Sarah could see the room filled with them, wearing the same slave clothes as herself."

    old "Judging by their skin, their hair, their eyes, nearly all of them were from Rosanna."
    new "Judging by their skin, their hair, their eyes, nearly all of them were from Rosanna."

    old "Perhaps even just that was a statement aimed at her."
    new "Perhaps even just that was a statement aimed at her."

    old "A reminder from the Khan to her of where the stood. What had become of her. Her people."
    new "A reminder from the Khan to her of where the stood. What had become of her. Her people."

    old "Not her people. Not anymore. She had failed them and no right to such a title."
    new "Not her people. Not anymore. She had failed them and no right to such a title."

    old "Standing near a group of Tribesmen, Sarah saw a young woman not too far from herself in age."
    new "Standing near a group of Tribesmen, Sarah saw a young woman not too far from herself in age."

    old "Clad in the same humiliating clothes, she poured wine from a pitcher into the cup of one of the soldiers."
    new "Clad in the same humiliating clothes, she poured wine from a pitcher into the cup of one of the soldiers."

    old "What had been her dreams, only a few weeks ago?"
    new "What had been her dreams, only a few weeks ago?"

    old "Had she grown up on a farm, hoping to marry one of the men from her village?"
    new "Had she grown up on a farm, hoping to marry one of the men from her village?"

    old "Had she lived in a city, perhaps hoping to inherit her father's business?"
    new "Had she lived in a city, perhaps hoping to inherit her father's business?"

    old "Whatever her hopes or dreams had been, Sarah knew for certain that this was not one of them."
    new "Whatever her hopes or dreams had been, Sarah knew for certain that this was not one of them."

    old "She watched as the Tribesman reached out and slapped the girl on her ass."
    new "She watched as the Tribesman reached out and slapped the girl on her ass."

    old "In this place, that was all the thanks a slave could expect for a job well done."
    new "In this place, that was all the thanks a slave could expect for a job well done."

    old "Sarah could see the girl's face."
    new "Sarah could see the girl's face."

    old "Rage. Sadness. Self-control."
    new "Rage. Sadness. Self-control."

    old "Sarah could have imagined any of those emotions on the girl's face, given her treatment."
    new "Sarah could have imagined any of those emotions on the girl's face, given her treatment."

    old "But instead, Sarah found on her face the same expression she found on most slaves."
    new "But instead, Sarah found on her face the same expression she found on most slaves."

    old "Muted. As if a fire had been snuffed out from behind their eyes."
    new "Muted. As if a fire had been snuffed out from behind their eyes."

    old "The outrage of being made to parade near naked. To serve their conquerors. To endure their humilations."
    new "The outrage of being made to parade near naked. To serve their conquerors. To endure their humilations."

    old "It was enough to bring anyone to rage."
    new "It was enough to bring anyone to rage."

    old "But it never did. Instead, each of the slaves yearned for the same thing all others did."
    new "But it never did. Instead, each of the slaves yearned for the same thing all others did."

    old "Survive. They wanted to be alive more than anything else."
    new "Survive. They wanted to be alive more than anything else."

    old "And in this place, that meant enduring what the Tribesmen inflicted. Accepting their place in this new world."
    new "And in this place, that meant enduring what the Tribesmen inflicted. Accepting their place in this new world."

    old "Sarah saw the girl being grabbed by the wrist, pulled down onto the lap of the soldier."
    new "Sarah saw the girl being grabbed by the wrist, pulled down onto the lap of the soldier."

    old "Her pitcher clattered to the floor."
    new "Her pitcher clattered to the floor."

    old "Nobody paid it much mind. The same scene seemed to play out all over the room."
    new "Nobody paid it much mind. The same scene seemed to play out all over the room."

    old "Happy soldiers and their spoils of war."
    new "Happy soldiers and their spoils of war."

    old "She watched as the girl leaned in and kissed the soldier."
    new "She watched as the girl leaned in and kissed the soldier."

    old "Easier that way, Sarah thought. He would have her anyway, if she smiled or cried over it, made no difference."
    new "Easier that way, Sarah thought. He would have her anyway, if she smiled or cried over it, made no difference."

    old "Look ahead."
    new "Look ahead."

    old "Sarah turned her eyes away from the sight."
    new "Sarah turned her eyes away from the sight."

    old "We are near to the Khan."
    new "We are near to the Khan."

    old "Do not forget to pay him the proper respects."
    new "Do not forget to pay him the proper respects."

    old "Jaeid had done his best to prepare her for the evening."
    new "Jaeid had done his best to prepare her for the evening."

    old "Hail, Khan Hassar."
    new "Hail, Khan Hassar."

    old "Sarah watched the Khan leaned back in his vast throne, smiling."
    new "Sarah watched the Khan leaned back in his vast throne, smiling."

    old "Aah, Jaeid. I am glad to see you here tonight."
    new "Aah, Jaeid. I am glad to see you here tonight."

    old "As if he had a choice, thought Sarah."
    new "As if he had a choice, thought Sarah."

    old "She saw the Khan's eyes slowly move from Jaeid to her."
    new "She saw the Khan's eyes slowly move from Jaeid to her."

    old "And you have brought a guest as well."
    new "And you have brought a guest as well."

    old "A test, thought Sarah. To see if she would claim to titles now stripped."
    new "A test, thought Sarah. To see if she would claim to titles now stripped."

    old "She knew what to do."
    new "She knew what to do."

    old "Sarah fell to her knees and planted her face to the ground, resting her hands in front of her."
    new "Sarah fell to her knees and planted her face to the ground, resting her hands in front of her."

    old "Ooh, great Khan, forgive me but I make claim to neither titles nor land."
    new "Ooh, great Khan, forgive me but I make claim to neither titles nor land."

    old "I am a slave to your Tribe."
    new "I am a slave to your Tribe."

    old "You honour me too much when you speak of me as a princess."
    new "You honour me too much when you speak of me as a princess."

    old "When she raised up her head, slowly, she saw the Khan grinning."
    new "When she raised up her head, slowly, she saw the Khan grinning."

    old "Aah, of course. The slave Sarah Rose."
    new "Aah, of course. The slave Sarah Rose."

    old "Perhaps my mind is wandering in my old age."
    new "Perhaps my mind is wandering in my old age."

    old "The advisors next to him gave a sycophantic laugh."
    new "The advisors next to him gave a sycophantic laugh."

    old "Regardless, for tonight you will carry the honours of your master Jaeid."
    new "Regardless, for tonight you will carry the honours of your master Jaeid."

    old "You will be allowed to sit here upon the dais among the exalted."
    new "You will be allowed to sit here upon the dais among the exalted."

    old "Great Khan, I trust in your wisdom to bestow onto me, whichever you imagine is right."
    new "Great Khan, I trust in your wisdom to bestow onto me, whichever you imagine is right."

    old "The Khan waved his hand, dismissing her further prostration."
    new "The Khan waved his hand, dismissing her further prostration."

    old "Sarah stood up and looked at Jaeid."
    new "Sarah stood up and looked at Jaeid."

    old "Did I do good?"
    new "Did I do good?"

    old "Jaeid smiled and nodded."
    new "Jaeid smiled and nodded."

    old "You did perfect."
    new "You did perfect."

    old "He grabbed her by the arm and escorted her towards their seat."
    new "He grabbed her by the arm and escorted her towards their seat."

    old "Together, they sat down at the table."
    new "Together, they sat down at the table."

    old "Every table in the room was overflowing with food and drink, but this table, the most exalted of all, was richer still."
    new "Every table in the room was overflowing with food and drink, but this table, the most exalted of all, was richer still."

    old "Sarah hestitantly began to eat as she studied the room further."
    new "Sarah hestitantly began to eat as she studied the room further."

    old "The others at the Khan's table were either advisors or members of his family."
    new "The others at the Khan's table were either advisors or members of his family."

    old "Regardless of which they were, they were all dressed in stunning clothes and outfits."
    new "Regardless of which they were, they were all dressed in stunning clothes and outfits."

    old "By contrast, Sarah herself stood out clearly with her slave clothing."
    new "By contrast, Sarah herself stood out clearly with her slave clothing."

    old "She could hear the other women whisper, pointing at her."
    new "She could hear the other women whisper, pointing at her."

    old "Sarah smiled as she took another bite of food."
    new "Sarah smiled as she took another bite of food."

    old "Why are you smiling?"
    new "Why are you smiling?"

    old "Those girls, they're gossiping."
    new "Those girls, they're gossiping."

    old "So?"
    new "So?"

    old "I just thought it was funny that some things are not so different between your people and mine."
    new "I just thought it was funny that some things are not so different between your people and mine."

    old "Jaeid softly laughed."
    new "Jaeid softly laughed."

    old "You are a strange one, Sarah Rose."
    new "You are a strange one, Sarah Rose."

    old "Sarah watched as Jaeid extended a small plate filled with food to her."
    new "Sarah watched as Jaeid extended a small plate filled with food to her."

    old "Food."
    new "Food."

    old "I know that but...why are you giving me this?"
    new "I know that but...why are you giving me this?"

    old "She saw Jaeid's face turn into one of embarrassment."
    new "She saw Jaeid's face turn into one of embarrassment."

    old "I...just...forget it!"
    new "I...just...forget it!"

    old "She heard him fumbling over his words."
    new "She heard him fumbling over his words."

    old "Only then did she realize he had simply tried to be kind."
    new "Only then did she realize he had simply tried to be kind."

    old "No, forget it, it is fine."
    new "No, forget it, it is fine."

    old "Please, give me the plate, I'll try some, I promise."
    new "Please, give me the plate, I'll try some, I promise."

    old "You don't have to just to spare me my feelings."
    new "You don't have to just to spare me my feelings."

    old "But I want to."
    new "But I want to."

    old "Sure, here."
    new "Sure, here."

    old "He pushed the plate of food back to her."
    new "He pushed the plate of food back to her."

    old "This time, Sarah politely ate what had been offered."
    new "This time, Sarah politely ate what had been offered."

    old "Jaeid had shared food with her before, but here in the Khan's palace, the food was of an altogether different quality."
    new "Jaeid had shared food with her before, but here in the Khan's palace, the food was of an altogether different quality."

    old "Sarah tasted flavors she had never before imagined or encountered."
    new "Sarah tasted flavors she had never before imagined or encountered."

    old "This is incredible!"
    new "This is incredible!"

    old "Yes...that is why I wanted to share it with you."
    new "Yes...that is why I wanted to share it with you."

    old "Sarah smiled at Jaeid."
    new "Sarah smiled at Jaeid."

    old "Then suddenly, she leaned in and hugged him."
    new "Then suddenly, she leaned in and hugged him."

    old "Perhaps in this new world this was far from appropriate, but Sarah could not contain herself."
    new "Perhaps in this new world this was far from appropriate, but Sarah could not contain herself."

    old "You are a kind person, Jaeid."
    new "You are a kind person, Jaeid."

    old "I want you to know that."
    new "I want you to know that."

    old "She saw him still flustered."
    new "She saw him still flustered."

    old "He was a man who found it easier to do good than to be given credit for doing good."
    new "He was a man who found it easier to do good than to be given credit for doing good."

    old "Jaeid quickly mumbled something, hoping to change the subject."
    new "Jaeid quickly mumbled something, hoping to change the subject."

    old "How are you doing so far?"
    new "How are you doing so far?"

    old "I'm fine now...when we entered and I saw the women...it was hard for a moment."
    new "I'm fine now...when we entered and I saw the women...it was hard for a moment."

    old "Jaeid looked across the room."
    new "Jaeid looked across the room."

    old "Yes...all from Rosanna I imagine. Such is often tradition, that the conquered women organize the feast to celebrate their own defeat."
    new "Yes...all from Rosanna I imagine. Such is often tradition, that the conquered women organize the feast to celebrate their own defeat."

    old "As I said, the Tribes enjoy their humiliation nearly as much as their conquest."
    new "As I said, the Tribes enjoy their humiliation nearly as much as their conquest."

    old "But it's fine...well, not this but...I think I can manage my emotions. At least for the night."
    new "But it's fine...well, not this but...I think I can manage my emotions. At least for the night."

    old "Still, stay on your guard. I doubt this is all they will try tonight."
    new "Still, stay on your guard. I doubt this is all they will try tonight."

    old "Sarah shivered."
    new "Sarah shivered."

    old "So much danger, constantly, it was hard to always remain vigilant enough."
    new "So much danger, constantly, it was hard to always remain vigilant enough."

    old "Still, for as much as she tried to remain on her guard, Sarah found it easy sit there with Jaeid."
    new "Still, for as much as she tried to remain on her guard, Sarah found it easy sit there with Jaeid."

    old "Out of everyone she had met, he seemed to be the only one who treated her as anything other than a slave."
    new "Out of everyone she had met, he seemed to be the only one who treated her as anything other than a slave."

    old "But there was also something else, though she found it hard to put her finger on."
    new "But there was also something else, though she found it hard to put her finger on."

    old "A general easiness of being. Their conversations flowed naturally. He made her forget the rest of the hall."
